main event: A witness observed a silvery disc-shaped object in Silver Springs, Maryland, for approximately 10 minutes on April 16, 1967.
interesting points: The sighting occurred in clear weather conditions,The object was described as solid and silver in color,The witness reported the object initially being stationary before it increased speed and departed,The witness was a 27-year-old male who provided additional details about the sighting,There was no photograph available in the report.
